        </Placemark>
        <Placemark>
          <name>Needles Cable Ferry</name>
          <description>
        &lt;![CDATA[
        &lt;h3&gt;🚢 Needles Cable Ferry&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Needles cable ferry runs across the Lower Arrow Lake, about 59 kilometres south of Nakusp on Highway 6, between Fauquier (east side) and Needles (west side).&lt;/p&gt;
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Vessel Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt; Unnamed&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Vehicle Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 40&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Passenger Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 135&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Crossing Time:&lt;/b&gt; 5 minutes&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Weight Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 276000 kg&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Schedule Type:&lt;/b&gt; Split Schedule 24hr - Demand at Night&lt;br/&gt;
            
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Schedule Information&lt;/h4&gt;
        Service hours:  From Fauquier*  5:00 am &amp;ndash; 10:00 pm    From Needles*  5:15 am &amp;ndash; 9:45 pm    On demand  10:00 pm &amp;ndash; 5:00 am   *Every 30 minutes
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Contact Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Organization:&lt;/b&gt; WaterBridge Ferries Inc.&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 2502652105&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Live Webcams&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;a href='https://prd-images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/860.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/442.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/1027.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/1043.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/1028.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Last Updated:&lt;/b&gt; 2026-03-18T16:00:32.373935-07:00&lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/transportation/passenger-travel/water-travel/inland-ferries/needles-cable-ferry&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More Information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        ]]&gt;
        </description>
          <styleUrl>#style_FERRY_CABLE</styleUrl>
          <Point>
            <coordinates>-118.09032599,49.87306207,0</coordinates>
          </Point>
        </Placemark>
      </Folder>
      <Folder>
        <name>On-Demand Ferries</name>
        <Placemark>
          <name>Barnston Island Ferry</name>
          <description>
        &lt;![CDATA[
        &lt;h3&gt;🚢 Barnston Island Ferry&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Barnston Island ferry runs across Parsons Channel on the south side of the Fraser River between Barnston Island (north bank) and Port Kells (south bank). Port Kells is in the northeast corner of Surrey at the bottom of 104th avenue.&lt;/p&gt;
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Vessel Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt; Unnamed&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Vehicle Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 5&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Passenger Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 52&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Crossing Time:&lt;/b&gt; 5 minutes&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Weight Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 40000 kg&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Schedule Type:&lt;/b&gt; On Demand Morning to Night&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Special Restrictions:&lt;/b&gt; Trucks with a GVW in excess of 20,000kg will be transported separately from other passengers and vehicles.&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Schedule Information&lt;/h4&gt;
        Service hours:  On demand, Monday &amp;ndash; Thursday  6:15 am &amp;ndash; 11:55 pm*    On demand, Friday &amp;ndash; Sunday  6:15 am &amp;ndash; 12:55 am*   *Service is interrupted as/when river traffic warrants.
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Contact Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Organization:&lt;/b&gt; Western Pacific Marine&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 6046815199&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Live Webcams&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/983.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/986.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/985.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Last Updated:&lt;/b&gt; 2026-03-18T16:00:32.385881-07:00&lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/transportation/passenger-travel/water-travel/inland-ferries/barnston-island-ferry&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More Information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        ]]&gt;
        </description>
          <styleUrl>#style_FERRY_ON_DEMAND</styleUrl>
          <Point>
            <coordinates>-122.72476444,49.19217855,0</coordinates>
          </Point>
        </Placemark>
        <Placemark>
          <name>Big Bar Reaction Ferry</name>
          <description>
        &lt;![CDATA[
        &lt;h3&gt;🚢 Big Bar Reaction Ferry&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Big Bar ferry runs across the Fraser River, 72 kilometres west of Clinton. When water is low or icy, an aerial tramway operates for passengers only.&lt;/p&gt;
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Vessel Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt; Unnamed&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Vehicle Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; N/A&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Passenger Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 12&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Crossing Time:&lt;/b&gt; 10 minutes&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Weight Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; N/A kg&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Schedule Type:&lt;/b&gt; On Demand Morning to Evening With Gaps&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Special Restrictions:&lt;/b&gt; Ferry capacity is 10 tonnes GVW and 12 passengers, including drivers. Vehicle combination cannot exceed 12 metres.&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Schedule Information&lt;/h4&gt;
        Service hours:  On demand  7:00 am &amp;ndash; noon 1:00 pm &amp;ndash; 5:00 pm 6:00 pm &amp;ndash; 7:00 pm
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Contact Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Organization:&lt;/b&gt; Dawson Road Maintenance&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Alt Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 18008424122&lt;br/&gt;
        
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Last Updated:&lt;/b&gt; 2026-03-18T16:00:32.458015-07:00&lt;/p&gt;
        
