      <Folder>
        <name>Scheduled Ferries</name>
        <Placemark>
          <name>Francois Lake Ferry</name>
          <description>
        &lt;![CDATA[
        &lt;h3&gt;🚢 Francois Lake Ferry&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The MV Francois Forester runs across Francois Lake on Highway 35, about 26 kilometres south of Burns Lake, from the community of Francois Lake (north side) to Southbank (south side).&lt;/p&gt;
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Vessel Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt; M.V. Francois Forester&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Vehicle Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 52&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Passenger Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 145&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Crossing Time:&lt;/b&gt; 15 minutes&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Weight Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 522000 kg&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Schedule Type:&lt;/b&gt; Scheduled Sailings Morning to Night&lt;br/&gt;
            
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Schedule Information&lt;/h4&gt;
        Service hours:  From south side  5:30 am &amp;ndash; 10:30 pm    From north side  5:55 am &amp;ndash; 11:00 pm   View detailed schedule
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Contact Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Organization:&lt;/b&gt; Waterbridge Equipment Ltd.&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 2506956491&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Live Webcams&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/140.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/1083.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Last Updated:&lt;/b&gt; 2026-03-18T16:00:32.406016-07:00&lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/transportation/passenger-travel/water-travel/inland-ferries/francois-lake-ferry&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More Information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        ]]&gt;
        </description>
          <styleUrl>#style_FERRY_SCHEDULED</styleUrl>
          <Point>
            <coordinates>-125.76435567,54.03943054,0</coordinates>
          </Point>
        </Placemark>
        <Placemark>
          <name>Kootenay Lake Ferry</name>
          <description>
        &lt;![CDATA[
        &lt;h3&gt;🚢 Kootenay Lake Ferry&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Kootenay Lake ferry runs across Kootenay Lake, 35 kilometres east of Nelson on Highway 3A, between Balfour (west side) and Kootenay Bay (east side), 70 kilometres from Creston on Highway 3A.&lt;/p&gt;
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Vessel Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt; M.V. Osprey 2000&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Vehicle Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 70&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Passenger Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 144&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Crossing Time:&lt;/b&gt; 35 minutes&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Weight Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 430000 kg&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Schedule Type:&lt;/b&gt; Scheduled Sailings Morning to Night&lt;br/&gt;
            
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Schedule Information&lt;/h4&gt;
        Service hours (M.V. Osprey 2000): The M.V. Osprey runs the regular winter schedule except when it is down for regular maintenance.&amp;nbsp; At that time the M.V. Balfour will service the run with it&amp;rsquo;s reduced capacity of 28 vehicles  From Balfour  6:30 am &amp;ndash; 9:40 pm    From Kootenay Bay  7:10 am &amp;ndash; 10:20 pm   View detailed schedule
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Contact Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Organization:&lt;/b&gt; Western Pacific Marine&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 2502295650&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Alt Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 2502294215&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Live Webcams&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/304.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/1031.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/303.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/1030.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Last Updated:&lt;/b&gt; 2026-03-18T16:00:32.498929-07:00&lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/transportation/passenger-travel/water-travel/inland-ferries/kootenay-lake-ferry&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More Information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        ]]&gt;
        </description>
          <styleUrl>#style_FERRY_SCHEDULED</styleUrl>
          <Point>
            <coordinates>-116.91473092,49.65006402,0</coordinates>
          </Point>
        </Placemark>
        <Placemark>
          <name>Upper Arrow Lake Ferry</name>
          <description>
        &lt;![CDATA[
        &lt;h3&gt;🚢 Upper Arrow Lake Ferry&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The M.V. Columbia runs across Upper Arrow Lake, 49 kilometres south of Revelstoke on Highway 23, between Shelter Bay (west side) and Galena Bay (east side).&lt;/p&gt;
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Vessel Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt; M.V. Columbia&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Vehicle Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 80&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Passenger Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 250&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Crossing Time:&lt;/b&gt; 20 minutes&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Weight Capacity:&lt;/b&gt; 714000 kg&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Schedule Type:&lt;/b&gt; Scheduled Sailings Morning to Night&lt;br/&gt;
            
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Schedule Information&lt;/h4&gt;
        Service hours:  From Shelter Bay  5 am - midnight    From Galena Bay  5:30 am - 12:30 am   View detailed schedule Refuelling: Ferry refuelling happens every Wednesday at 8:45 am. There may be minor delays for one or two sailings directly following refuelling. Dangerous cargo: Tuesdays and Thursdays (except statutory holidays) are reserved for dangerous cargo.  From Shelter Bay  9:00 am 2:00 pm    From Galena Bay  9:30 am 2:30 pm   Passenger limits with dangerous cargo:  Explosives  12 passengers    Other dangerous cargo  25 passengers   Transporting dangerous goods
        
        
            &lt;h4&gt;Contact Information&lt;/h4&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Organization:&lt;/b&gt; WaterBridge Ferries Inc.&lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;b&gt;Phone:&lt;/b&gt; 2502652105&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;h4&gt;Live Webcams&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/188.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/518.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/969.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/481.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href='https://images.drivebc.ca/bchighwaycam/pub/cameras/482.jpg' target='_blank'&gt;Webcam 5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Last Updated:&lt;/b&gt; 2026-03-18T16:00:32.352420-07:00&lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/transportation/passenger-travel/water-travel/inland-ferries/upper-arrow-lake-ferry&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;More Information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        ]]&gt;
        </description>
